# Intuition ğŸ¤”ğŸ’¡  
Imagine drawing a **spiral** ğŸŒ€ on a whiteboard! We start from the **top-left** and move **right** â¡, then **down** â¬‡, then **left** â¬…, and finally **up** â¬†. We keep repeating this pattern while shrinking the boundaries until we visit all elements.  

# Approach ğŸš€ğŸ›¤  
1. Define four boundaries:  
   - `left` ğŸ (starting column)  
   - `right` ğŸ (ending column)  
   - `top` ğŸš€ (starting row)  
   - `bottom` ğŸš€ (ending row)  

2. Use a direction variable `id` ğŸ”„ to track movement:  
   - `id = 0` â†’ **Move Left to Right** â¡  
   - `id = 1` â†’ **Move Top to Bottom** â¬‡  
   - `id = 2` â†’ **Move Right to Left** â¬…  
   - `id = 3` â†’ **Move Bottom to Top** â¬†  

3. After completing a direction, **shrink the boundary** ğŸ”¥.  
4. Repeat until all elements are added to the result list âœ….  

# Complexity â³ğŸ’»  
- **Time complexity:** $$O(m \times n)$$ â†’ We visit each element **once**.  
- **Space complexity:** $$O(1)$$ â†’ We use only a result list, no extra storage.  

# Code ğŸ‘¨â€ğŸ’»ğŸ¯  
```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> spiralOrder(vector<vector<int>>& matrix) {
        vector<int> res;
        int rows = matrix.size();
        int cols = matrix[0].size();

        int left = 0, right = cols - 1, top = 0, bottom = rows - 1;
        int id = 0;

        /*
        ğŸ”„ Directions:
        id = 0 â†’ Move left to right â¡
        id = 1 â†’ Move top to bottom â¬‡
        id = 2 â†’ Move right to left â¬…
        id = 3 â†’ Move bottom to top â¬†
        */

        while (left <= right && top <= bottom) {
            if (id == 0) { // â¡ Move Left to Right
                for (int i = left; i <= right; i++) {
                    res.push_back(matrix[top][i]);
                }
                top++; // Shrink top boundary ğŸš€
            } 
            else if (id == 1) { // â¬‡ Move Top to Bottom
                for (int i = top; i <= bottom; i++) {
                    res.push_back(matrix[i][right]);
                }
                right--; // Shrink right boundary ğŸ¯
            } 
            else if (id == 2) { // â¬… Move Right to Left
                for (int i = right; i >= left; i--) {
                    res.push_back(matrix[bottom][i]);
                }
                bottom--; // Shrink bottom boundary ğŸ”¥
            } 
            else if (id == 3) { // â¬† Move Bottom to Top
                for (int i = bottom; i >= top; i--) {
                    res.push_back(matrix[i][left]);
                }
                left++; // Shrink left boundary ğŸ
            }
            id = (id + 1) % 4; // Cycle through directions ğŸ”„
        }
        return res;
    }
};
